# Force sharp to use its bundled prebuilt binary instead of attempting
# to link against a globally-installed libvips.
#
# Why this exists: sharp@0.34.5 is pulled in transitively by miniflare
# (via wrangler → @cloudflare/vite-plugin). On `npm install`, sharp's
# install lifecycle (`install/check.js`) calls `useGlobalLibvips()`.
# That function checks pkg-config for a system libvips and, if found,
# returns true — which tells sharp to skip its just-downloaded prebuild
# and try to build from source. The build-from-source path then fails
# on missing node-gyp / node-addon-api peer deps and the whole npm
# install rolls back.
#
# Triggered by: any developer with `brew install vips` on macOS (image
# processing toolchain), or apt-installed libvips-dev on Linux.
# Untriggered: clean dev machines and CI runners (no pkg-config match).
#
# The right answer is "use the prebuild that's right there in
# node_modules/@img/sharp-<platform>"; setting this env var locks in
# that behavior.
#
# Upstream issue: TODO (creek will file)
SHARP_IGNORE_GLOBAL_LIBVIPS=1
